---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from 'astrowind:config';

const metadata = {
  title: `Quality & Inspection Lab — R&D Center — ${SITE.name}`,
  description: `${SITE.name} Quality & Inspection Lab: tensile testing, air-retention cycling, seam peel tests, material certification. ISO-compliant quality assurance for inflatable boats and RIBs.`,
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <section class="px-6 sm:px-6 py-16 sm:py-20 mx-auto max-w-5xl">
    <a href="/randdcenter" class="text-sm text-gray-500 hover:underline">&larr; Back to R&D Center</a>
    <div class="mt-4 grid md:grid-cols-5 gap-10">
      <div class="md:col-span-3">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-primary uppercase tracking-wider">Lab 06</p>
        <h1 class="mt-2 text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold">Quality & Inspection Lab</h1>
        <p class="mt-3 text-lg text-muted">Independent verification — every test passed before delivery</p>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-2">
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1581092918056-0c4c3acd3789?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&auto=format&fit=crop&w=870&q=80" alt="Quality inspection laboratory" class="w-full h-48 object-cover rounded-xl" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="px-6 sm:px-6 pb-12 mx-auto max-w-4xl prose prose-gray dark:prose-invert">
    <h2>Trust, but verify</h2>
    <p>
      Every boat that leaves our workshop carries the certification that it has passed a defined set of quality 
      inspections and material tests. Our Quality & Inspection Lab is an independent function within the organisation — 
      it reports directly to the managing director, not to production — ensuring that no commercial pressure can 
      compromise the inspection gate. If a material batch or a completed boat does not meet the published specification, 
      the lab has the authority to halt shipment until the non-conformance is resolved.
    </p>
    <p>
      The lab operates under a quality management system aligned with ISO 9001:2015 principles, and our test methods 
      are based on ISO, ASTM, and EN standards wherever applicable. We maintain detailed records of every test performed, 
      creating a complete traceability chain from raw material receipt to final boat delivery.
    </p>

    <h2>Test equipment and capabilities</h2>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Equipment</th><th>Tests Performed</th><th>Standard / Method</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Universal testing machine (50 kN)</td><td>Tensile strength (fabric), peel resistance (seams), tear propagation</td><td>ISO 1421, ISO 2411, ISO 4674</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Air-retention test rig (programmable)</td><td>1000-cycle inflation/deflation endurance, 30 min pressure-hold test</td><td>ISO 6185 (internal)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Seam-peel jig (motorised 180&deg; peel)</td><td>Weld and glued-seam peel strength at 100 mm/min</td><td>ISO 2411 / ASTM D1876</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Hydrostatic head tester</td><td>Water penetration resistance of fabric (0–500 mbar)</td><td>ISO 811</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Digital thickness gauge &amp; micrometre</td><td>Fabric thickness, tube wall thickness, adhesive-film thickness</td><td>ISO 2286-3</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Environmental chamber</td><td>Temperature conditioning (-40 &deg;C to +80 &deg;C) for cold-crack and heat-ageing tests</td><td>ISO 188, ISO 4675</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Colour spectrophotometer</td><td>Delta-E colour measurement after UV exposure</td><td>ISO 105-A05 / ASTM D2244</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>The inspection gates — from material to delivery</h2>
    <p>
      Every boat follows a defined quality plan with mandatory inspection points. No boat can skip a gate; each gate 
      must be signed off by a quality inspector before the next production stage begins.
    </p>

    <div class="not-prose my-8">
      <div class="relative">
        <div class="absolute left-4 top-0 bottom-0 w-0.5 bg-blue-200 dark:bg-blue-800"></div>
        <div class="space-y-6 relative">
          {[
            { gate: 'Gate 1', label: 'Incoming material inspection', desc: 'Fabric batch, adhesive batch, hardware — all checked against incoming specification before release to production.' },
            { gate: 'Gate 2', label: 'In-process weld inspection', desc: 'First-off weld coupon tested (peel + visual) at start of each production shift.' },
            { gate: 'Gate 3', label: 'Chamber air test', desc: 'Each chamber pressurised to 1.5 x working pressure, held 30 min. Data logged per serial number.' },
            { gate: 'Gate 4', label: 'Pre-delivery inspection', desc: 'Complete boat inspected: all fasteners torqued, systems functional, no cosmetic defects. 100-point checklist.' },
            { gate: 'Gate 5', label: 'Final certification', desc: 'Test reports compiled, inspection records reviewed, Certificate of Conformance issued.' },
          ].map((g) => (
            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-blue-600 text-white flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold z-10">{g.gate}</div>
              <div class="flex-1 p-3 rounded-lg bg-white dark:bg-gray-950 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800">
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold">{g.label}</p>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1">{g.desc}</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Key quality metrics (2025 rolling average)</h2>
    <div class="not-prose my-8 grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
      <div class="p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 bg-white dark:bg-gray-950 text-center">
        <span class="block text-2xl font-bold text-blue-600">99.7 %</span>
        <span class="text-xs text-gray-500">First-pass yield (fabric batch)</span>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 bg-white dark:bg-gray-950 text-center">
        <span class="block text-2xl font-bold text-blue-600">&lt; 0.2 %</span>
        <span class="text-xs text-gray-500">Weld reject rate (linear metre)</span>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 bg-white dark:bg-gray-950 text-center">
        <span class="block text-2xl font-bold text-blue-600">100 %</span>
        <span class="text-xs text-gray-500">Chambers air-tested before assembly</span>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 bg-white dark:bg-gray-950 text-center">
        <span class="block text-2xl font-bold text-blue-600">ISO 6185</span>
        <span class="text-xs text-gray-500">Design category compliance</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Our quality team</h2>
    <p>
      The lab is staffed by a quality manager (10 years in marine QA, ASQ Certified Quality Engineer), two quality 
      inspectors (each with Level 2 NDT certification in visual testing), and a materials technician responsible for 
      all physical testing. The team undergoes annual proficiency testing through an independent third-party provider 
      to ensure that our test results remain accurate and reproducible.
    </p>

    <h2>Independent testing for clients</h2>
    <p>
      Our Quality & Inspection Lab is available for independent testing services. If you need to verify a fabric 
      specification, validate a new adhesive system, or obtain a third-party test report for a procurement 
      qualification, we can perform the tests to the applicable standard and issue a certified test report.
    </p>
    <p>
      Examples of recent third-party testing work:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Peel-strength comparison of five competitive adhesive film products for a European military procurement programme.</li>
      <li>Accelerated ageing study (UV + thermal cycling) for a new orange-pigmented PVC formulation, with regular 
      interim measurements at 500 h intervals.</li>
      <li>Air-retention validation of 50 prototype baffle valves for a new high-pressure tube design.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Our commitment to you</h2>
    <p>
      When you receive a {SITE.name} boat, you also receive its quality dossier — a compiled record of the test 
      results that apply to your specific boat. Fabric batch certificate, weld peel tests, chamber air-test logs, 
      and pre-delivery inspection checklist. Every number is traceable. Every inspector is identified. This is not 
      just paperwork — it is our promise that what we delivered is what we specified.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you ever have a quality concern, you can contact the lab directly — the contact details are printed on 
      your certificate of conformance. We take every query seriously and commit to a formal investigation within 
      48 hours.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="px-6 sm:px-6 pb-20 mx-auto max-w-4xl text-center">
    <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900 p-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold">Need independent testing or quality verification?</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted">Our lab accepts third-party testing work — contact us with your requirements.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="mt-4 inline-block px-6 py-3 bg-primary text-white font-semibold rounded-md hover:bg-primary/90">Contact the quality lab</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
